div.font:
Known to others / you
Things known to you and everyone around you.
Example: a good grade in Math tells you, that you are good in Math and everyone else knows they can ask you for help in Math.

div.font:
Unknown to you / known to others
Things that you are not aware of but others are.
Example: body language you often use, body odour, slower working pace than colleagues.
If no feedback is given, the person will not change their behaviour

switch.text: Unknown to you / known to others...

div.font:
Known only to yourself
Things only you know but others don't.
Example: hobby you don't want to share yet, Experiences from the past, family values, fears, aspirations.
This window gets smaller the more the person shares with the people around them, thus the Open Self window gets bigger.
